catter, down to the smallest\nradii where deprojection is straightforward ($\\sim 20$ kpc); within this\nradius, even the most relaxed systems show clear departures from spherical\nsymmetry. Our results suggest that heating and cooling are continuously\nregulated in a tight feedback loop, allowing the cluster atmosphere to remain\nstratified on these scales.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 4 Sep 2015 01:44:44 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 4 Jan 2016 21:15:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-01-18"}
